316
00:35:17,152 --> 00:35:17,873
No need.

317
00:35:43,793 --> 00:35:46,192
One question's haunted me.

318
00:35:47,513 --> 00:35:48,112
Yes?

319
00:35:48,592 --> 00:35:51,192
Why are there five coins
hanging down here?

320
00:35:52,033 --> 00:35:53,033
Five Emperor Coins.

321
00:35:53,833 --> 00:35:54,833
Round and square.

322
00:35:55,592 --> 00:35:56,592
Cosmic unity.

323
00:35:56,993 --> 00:35:58,072
They ward off evil.

324
00:36:00,232 --> 00:36:00,873
What?

325
00:36:01,793 --> 00:36:02,793
Do you think

326
00:36:04,033 --> 00:36:05,793
I've ruined the integrity
of your artwork?

327
00:36:07,232 --> 00:36:08,473
Not exactly 'ruined.'

328
00:36:09,353 --> 00:36:10,873
Hermit Duck was my early creation.

329
00:36:11,152 --> 00:36:12,513
It accidentally turned out well.

330
00:36:13,033 --> 00:36:15,072
No systematic creative philosophy
is behind it.

331
00:36:16,152 --> 00:36:17,953
I just feel they don't match well.

332
00:36:24,953 --> 00:36:25,752
A hermit

333
00:36:26,473 --> 00:36:27,752
retreats from worldly affairs,

334
00:36:28,953 --> 00:36:31,152
free from fame and wealth
and content with simplicity.

335
00:36:33,433 --> 00:36:36,913
Ducks sense the warmth
of spring rivers first.

336
00:36:37,793 --> 00:36:40,232
It's an image full of spring vitality,
warm and cozy.

337
00:36:41,793 --> 00:36:42,712
Five Emperor Coins

338
00:36:43,953 --> 00:36:46,632
attract fortune, wealth, peace, and joy.

339
00:36:48,913 --> 00:36:51,112
Hermit, duck, and coins.

340
00:36:51,552 --> 00:36:54,353
These three elements
complement each other.

341
00:36:54,833 --> 00:36:55,993
A perfect combination.

342
00:36:57,552 --> 00:36:59,513
You're pretending
to be knowledgeable again.

343
00:37:02,953 --> 00:37:05,552
I told you, you're an optimistic person.

344
00:37:08,712 --> 00:37:10,072
Since when does the heir

345
00:37:10,552 --> 00:37:12,272
